{"word":"H6601 - פָּתָה - pâthâh - paw-thaw' - Allure","slug":"H6601","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּתָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâthâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-thaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Allure"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05D4; - pa&#x0302;tha&#x0302;h</b> - <i>paw-thaw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>open</i>, that is, <i>be</i> (causatively <i>make</i>) <i>roomy</i>; usually figuratively (in a mental or moral sense) to <i>be</i> (causatively <i>make</i>) <i>simple</i> or (in a sinister way) <i>delude: - </i>allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly (one)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3315\">H3315</a>, <a href=\"#/H6602\">H6602</a>, <a href=\"#/H6604\">H6604</a>, <a href=\"#/H6612\">H6612</a>, <a href=\"#/H6615\">H6615</a>"}]}